Description: Fits boundary line models to datasets and making statistical 
    inferences about their parameters. Provides tools for testing datasets for evidence 
    of boundary presence, fitting boundary line models, and conducting post-hoc analyses 
    such as predicting boundary values and identifying the most limiting factor (Miti, 
    Milne, Giller, Lark (2024) <doi:10.1016/j.fcr.2024.109365>).
